title: Important Update About Medicaid and PeachCare for Kids® Coverage for Impacted MembersFebruary 05, 2026
body: . The .gov means it’s official. . “georgia.gov” or “ga.gov” at the end of the address. Before sharing sensitive or personal information, make sure you’re on an official state website. Still not sure? Call1-800-GEORGIAto verify that a website is an official website of the State of Georgia. February 05, 2026 A recent technical error caused some members of Georgia Medicaid and Peachcare for Kids® to be flagged incorrectly during a routine update. As a result, some members received termination notices or saw their coverage end in error. Cases that were incorrectly terminated will be reinstated as quickly as possible. The Department of Community Health is taking the following steps to address the issue: This error was not caused by any action taken by our members and does not reflect a change in the member’s eligibility. Medicaid and Peachcare for Kids® members do not need to submit a new application or take any additional steps at this time. If coverage was incorrectly terminated, it will be reinstated automatically. Any services received during the affected period will continue to be covered. We sincerely apologize for the stress and inconvenience this issue may have caused. Medicaid and Peachcare for Kids® members rely on consistent access to care, and we take that responsibility seriously. Members who have questions about this incident can contact Gainwell Technologies at 1-866-211-0950, Monday through Friday, 8 a.m. to 7 p.m. E.T.

Families in the Katie Beckett program rely on consistent access to care, and we take that responsibility seriously.

title: Rural Health Transformation Program Application Has Been SubmittedNovember 10, 2025
body: . The .gov means it’s official. . “georgia.gov” or “ga.gov” at the end of the address. Before sharing sensitive or personal information, make sure you’re on an official state website. Still not sure? Call1-800-GEORGIAto verify that a website is an official website of the State of Georgia. November 10, 2025 See Georgia's Application - Clickhere! The Georgia Department of Community Health is excited to announce that Georgia’s application for the federal Rural Health Transformation (RHT) Program has been submitted. After months of public input, including four townhalls and over 150 submitted ideas, the application compiled numerous proposals with the intent of creating lasting, transformative change to the rural health ecosystem in Georgia. This is the beginning of the process for the RHT Program grant. Further details on what entities may be eligible for each opportunity and application processes will be released at a later date. The Rural Health Transformation Program page,linked here, will continue to serve as the primary source of information sharing throughout this grant. CMS is set to notify states of their award by December 31, 2025. All official communications to the public regarding final awards will be posted to this page. Resources will be regularly updated on theDCH websiteand currently include the submitted application for public review, as well as additional letters of support, Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs) and other helpful information.

October 20, 2025 The Georgia Department of Administrative Services (DOAS), on behalf of the Georgia Department of Community Health (DCH), has issued a Notice of Intent to Award for the Pharmacy Benefit Services Request for Proposals (RFP #41900-DCH0000136) under the NASPO ValuePoint Cooperative Purchasing Program. Pharmacy Benefit Administrative Services Georgia served as the lead state for this multi-state procurement. The Notice of Intent to Award identifies apparent successful offerors across multiple service categories, including Pharmacy Benefit Administration, Clinical Management, Drug Rebate, and Fraud, Waste, and Abuse Services. DCH will conduct a down-select process to determine final vendor participation through a state-specific Participating Addendum (PA). For additional information regarding the Notice of Intent to Award and related documentation, please visitGeorgia Procurement Registry

title: Medicaid Members Offered Free Credit Monitoring After Possible Data BreachOctober 01, 2025
body: . The .gov means it’s official. . “georgia.gov” or “ga.gov” at the end of the address. Before sharing sensitive or personal information, make sure you’re on an official state website. Still not sure? Call1-800-GEORGIAto verify that a website is an official website of the State of Georgia. October 01, 2025 The Georgia Department of Community Health (DCH) and Gainwell Technologies are announcing that on July 23, 2025, an unauthorized telephone caller gained access to a reimbursement account for a healthcare provider’s Medicaid billing record. This access may have exposed the name, Medicaid member ID’s, coverage and payment information for claims and date ranges for when services were provided under Georgia Medicaid. Gainwell provides fiscal-agent services for the Medicaid program administered by DCH. DCH and Gainwell are committed to protecting the confidentiality and security of our customers’ personal information. That is why we are providingthisnoticeto make you aware of this event. Anyone whose information was found to be involved has been notified by mail. Letters were mailed on September 25, 2025. If you did not receive a letter stating that your information may have been compromised, but want to make sure you were not affected, please call IDX, a data breach and recovery services company, toll-free, at 1-833-788-9712. IDX will respond to questions about this event and can confirm if your information was affected.

October 01, 2025 Effective today, October 1, 2025, the approved extension of the Georgia Pathways to Coverage™ program will go into effect, allowing the program to continue through December 31, 2026. Key Updates Effective October 1: For more information about Pathways, visitpathways.georgia.gov. To apply, visitgateway.ga.gov. Applicants may also apply by phone at 1-877-423-4746 or 711 for those who are deaf, hard of hearing, deaf-blind, or have difficulty speaking; in-person at your local Division of Family & Children Services (DFCS) office:dfcs.ga.gov/locations; or by mail to your local DFCS office.

September 29, 2025 Effective October 1, 2025, Pathways members will be required to pay a copayment for certain services. Copayment amounts vary based upon the service. Please note,copayments for thePathways program align with those of all other Medicaid classes of assistance, as reflected in the State’s Medicaid plan. If you cannot pay the copayment, you may still receive services. Copayments are not required for Pathways members under age 21. See below for copayment amounts. $10.00 or less: $0.50 $10.01 to $25.00: $1.00 $25.01 to $50.00: $2.00 $50.01 or more: $3.00
